BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Kogx4soY-re9b4qI0ntz3
SUMMARY:Trauma Recovery Stories: Seattle
DTSTAMP:20260403T051339Z
DTSTART:20260409T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us on April 9\\\, 2026\\\, at the Lapis Theatre for the on
	e-night-only premiere of Trauma Recovery Stories: Seattle. \\n \\nThe film
	 follows three Seattle residents who have overcome different types of trau
	ma and whose stories intersect in the arts\\\, specifically poetry and mus
	ic. Donna Leigh is a pioneer in the LGBTQ+ community. Iz White is an enrol
	led member of the Snoqualmie Tribe who grew up in the aftermath of tragedy
	. Fantasy A is an artist whose relentless drive has pushed him beyond limi
	ts others once placed on him because of his autism diagnosis. \\n \\nThe s
	creening will be followed by live performances from Fantasy A\\\, Donna\\\
	, and Iz.  \\n \\nThis film is for anyone who has felt alone in what they 
	went through.  \\n \\nContent warning: discussion of childhood trauma\\\, 
	emotional abuse\\\, grief and loss\\\, addiction\\\, homelessness/instabil
	ity\\\, trans identity and discrimination\\\, and mental health. \\nFree a
	dmission to this event is made possible with support from 4Culture.\n\nhtt
	ps://hugohouse.org/event/trauma-recovery-stories-seattle-a-film-screening_
	2026-04-09/\n\nFrom Hugo House
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/trauma-recovery-stories-seattle-a-film-scre
	ening_2026-04-09/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hugo-house
CATEGORIES:Hugo House
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
